'''Pedro Antonio Porro Sauceda''' ({{IPA|es|peðɾo ˈporo}}; born 13 September 1999) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Oficial: Sporting aciona opção de compra por Porro |trans-title=Official: Sporting activate purchase option for Porro |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sporting/16-05-2022/oficial-sporting-aciona-opcao-de-compra-por-porro |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517102324/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sporting/16-05-2022/oficial-sporting-aciona-opcao-de-compra-por-porro |archive-date=17 May 2022 |access-date=17 May 2022 |website=Mais Futebol |language=pt}}</ref>

Porro started his career with [[Girona FC|Girona]]'s reserve team [[CF Peralada|Peralada]], before being promoted to the first team in 2017. In 2019, he signed for Premier League side [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for a reported fee of €13&nbsp;million (£11&nbsp;million). He was loaned to La Liga side [[Real Valladolid]] and then Portuguese Primeira Liga club Sporting on an initial two-year loan deal. With Sporting, he won a [[Double (association football)|double]] of the [[Primeira Liga]] and [[Taça da Liga]], while being named in the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Primeira Liga Team of the Year]]. His transfer was made permanent at the end of his second season.

Porro first appeared with the [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain under-21s]] in March 2019, aged 19. He made his senior international debut in 2021 and was included in the squad for the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals]] in Italy, in which Spain finished as runners-up.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Don Benito]], [[Province of Badajoz|Badajoz]], Extremadura, Porro represented Gimnástico de Don Benito and [[Rayo Vallecano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hoy.es/deportes/futbol/futuro-porro-pasa-20170815001136-ntvo.html|title=El futuro de Porro pasa por Girona|trans-title=The future of Porro goes through Girona|website=Hoy|language=es|date=15 August 2017|access-date=29 November 2017|archive-date=18 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718180953/https://www.hoy.es/deportes/futbol/futuro-porro-pasa-20170815001136-ntvo.html|url-status=live}}</ref> before joining [[Girona FC|Girona]] on 10 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/girona/2017/08/10/598c839b22601d51388b45d3.html|title=Pedro Porro, la nueva adquisición del Girona|trans-title=Pedro Porro, the new acquisition of Girona|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|publisher=Unidad Editorial|language=es|date=10 August 2017|access-date=29 November 2017|archive-date=22 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622173205/https://www.marca.com/futbol/girona/2017/08/10/598c839b22601d51388b45d3.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He reportedly rejected [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], [[Atlético Madrid]] and [[Bayern Munich]] to sign for the [[Catalonia|Catalans]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport.es/es/noticias/girona/juvenil-del-rayo-prefiere-fichar-por-girona-que-por-madrid-6222426|title=Un juvenil del Rayo prefiere fichar por el Girona que por el Madrid|trans-title=A ''juvenil'' from Rayo prefers to sign for Girona than for Madrid|newspaper=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|publisher=Ediciones Deportivas Catalanas, S.A.|language=es|date=13 August 2017|access-date=29 November 2017|archive-date=19 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719014757/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/girona/juvenil-del-rayo-prefiere-fichar-por-girona-que-por-madrid-6222426|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Girona===
On 28 November 2017, before even appearing with [[CF Peralada-Girona B|the reserves]], Porro made his first team debut by coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for goalscorer [[Johan Mojica]] in a 1–1 away draw against [[Levante UD|Levante]], for [[2017–18 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2017_18/copa/dieciseisavos/vuelta/lev_ger/|title=Morales no tira la Copa|trans-title=Morales does not take away the Cup|newspaper=Marca|location=Spain|publisher=Unidad Editorial|language=es|date=28 November 2017|access-date=29 November 2017|archive-date=22 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180922184026/http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2017_18/copa/dieciseisavos/vuelta/lev_ger|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first appearance for the B-side five days later, playing the last seven minutes in a 0–0 [[Segunda División B]] draw at [[CD Ebro|Ebro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hoy.es/deportes/futbol/liga-segunda-b/pedro-porro-estrena-20171205002756-ntvo.html|title=Pedro Porro se estrena también con el Girona en Segunda B|trans-title=Pedro Porro also debuts with Girona in Segunda B|website=Hoy|language=es|date=5 December 2017|access-date=21 December 2017|archive-date=25 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725033534/https://www.hoy.es/deportes/futbol/liga-segunda-b/pedro-porro-estrena-20171205002756-ntvo.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Porro scored his first senior goals on 6 May 2018, scoring twice in a 3–0 away win against [[Villarreal CF B|Villarreal B]]. On 2 July, he renewed his contract until 2022,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2018/07/02/mundial/1530549653_448942.html|title=El Girona blinda a su perla Pedro Porro: renueva hasta 2022|trans-title=Girona tie up their pearl Pedro Porro: renews until 2022|newspaper=[[Diario AS]]|publisher=[[PRISA]]|language=es|date=2 July 2018|access-date=13 August 2018|archive-date=22 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622174453/https://as.com/futbol/2018/07/02/mundial/1530549653_448942.html|url-status=live}}</ref> and played most of the pre-season as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]]. Porro made his [[La Liga]] debut on 17 August 2018, starting as right back in a 0–0 home draw against [[Real Valladolid]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/2018/08/17/5b76f79b22601d596a8b4630.html|title=Ni VAR ni puntería|trans-title=Neither VAR nor aim|newspaper=Marca|location=Spain|publisher=Unidad Editorial|language=es|date=17 August 2018|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=24 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124210434/https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/2018/08/17/5b76f79b22601d596a8b4630.html|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, he extended his contract for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gironafc.cat/noticia/el-girona-fc-amplia-un-any-mes-el-contracte-de-pedro-porro-fins-el-2023|title=El Girona FC amplia un any més el contracte de Pedro Porro, fins el 2023|trans-title=Girona FC extend a further year the contract of Pedro Porro, until 2023|publisher=Girona FC|language=ca|date=18 August 2018|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=23 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191023051325/https://www.gironafc.cat/noticia/el-girona-fc-amplia-un-any-mes-el-contracte-de-pedro-porro-fins-el-2023|url-status=live}}</ref>

Porro established himself as a starter under [[Eusebio Sacristán]], becoming first choice ahead of [[Aday Benítez]] and replacing departed [[Pablo Maffeo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/deportes/20190125/pedro-porro-eusebio-girona-fc-barcelona-lateral-biografia-7267871|title=Pedro Porro, el nieto de Antonio|trans-title=Pedro Porro, the grandson of Antonio|newspaper=[[El Periódico (Barcelona)|El Periódico]]|publisher=[[Prensa Ibérica]]|language=es|date=25 January 2019|access-date=26 January 2019|archive-date=10 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310235429/https://www.elperiodico.com/es/deportes/20190125/pedro-porro-eusebio-girona-fc-barcelona-lateral-biografia-7267871|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 31 January 2019, his team's only goal in a 1–3 cup loss at [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/copa-rey/cronica/2019/01/31/5c5374cce2704e264e8b45c8.html|title=Benzema se exhibe en la Copa|trans-title=Benzema shows himself in the Cup|newspaper=Marca|location=Spain|publisher=Unidad Editorial|language=es|date=31 January 2019|access-date=2 February 2019|archive-date=23 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423035213/https://www.marca.com/futbol/copa-rey/cronica/2019/01/31/5c5374cce2704e264e8b45c8.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
On 8 August 2019, Porro signed for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gironafc.cat/noticia/el-manchester-city-fitxa-pedro-porro|title=El Manchester City fixta Pedro Porro|trans-title=Manchester City sign Pedro Porro|publisher=Girona FC|language=ca|date=8 August 2019|access-date=8 August 2019|archive-date=18 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418112909/https://www.gironafc.cat/noticia/el-manchester-city-fitxa-pedro-porro|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Millar |first=Colin |date=8 August 2019 |title=Manchester City sign Pedro Porro, loaned to Real Valladolid |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2019/08/08/manchester-city-sign-pedro-porro-loaned-to-real-valladolid |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=Football España |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 August 2019 |title=Man City 'agree £11m deal for Pedro Porro' |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/man-city/transfer-talk/news/man-city-agree-gbp11m-deal-for-pedro-porro_367429.html |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=Sports Mole |language=en-GB}}</ref> for a reported fee of £11&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mullock |first=Simon |date=8 August 2019 |title=Man City agree transfer deadline day deal for £11million defender |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-city-agree-transfer-deadline-18863140 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108003340/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-city-agree-transfer-deadline-18863140 |archive-date=8 November 2020 |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=Daily Mirror |language=en}}</ref>

==== Loan to Real Valladolid ====
Upon signing for Manchester City, Porro was immediately loaned to [[Real Valladolid]] in [[La Liga]] for one season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/actualidad/12082019/Pedro-Porro-fortalece-la-banda-derecha/|title=Pedro Porro fortalece la banda derecha|trans-title=Pedro Porro bolsters the right back|publisher=Real Valladolid|language=es|date=12 August 2019|accessdate=13 August 2019|archive-date=12 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812113205/http://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/actualidad/12082019/Pedro-Porro-fortalece-la-banda-derecha/|url-status=live}}</ref> The club had an option to make a permanent move, and after playing 13 league games, helping the ''Pucelanos'' to a 13th place finish, Real Valladolid opted to not exercise their option to sign Porro on a permanent basis.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Pedro Porro fortalece la banda derecha|url=https://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/actualidad/12082019/Pedro-Porro-fortalece-la-banda-derecha|url-status=dead|access-date=12 August 2019|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221016080022/https://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/actualidad/12082019/Pedro-Porro-fortalece-la-banda-derecha|archive-date=16 October 2022}}</ref>

=== Sporting CP ===
On 16 August 2020, Porro joined [[Sporting CP]] on a two-year loan deal until 30 June 2022 with the option of making the move permanent for €8.5&nbsp;million (£7&nbsp;million).<ref>{{Cite web|date=16 August 2020|title=Pedro Porro joins Sporting CP on loan|url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2020-08-16/pedro-porro-joins-sporting-cp-loan|access-date=16 August 2020|publisher=Sporting CP|archive-date=16 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200816080203/https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2020-08-16/pedro-porro-joins-sporting-cp-loan|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2020 |title=Pedro Porro joins Sporting CP on loan |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2020-08-16/pedro-porro-joins-sporting-cp-loan |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=sporting.pt |language=en}}</ref>

On 24 September 2020, he made his debut for the club in a 1–0 home win against [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|third qualifying round]] of the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Crighton |first=Chris |date=25 September 2020 |title=Fan view: Tiago Tomas' finish showed strength Sporting possess as Aberdeen suffer another Europa League near miss |url=https://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/fp/sport/football/aberdeen-fc/2518114/fan-view-tiago-tomas-finish-showed-strength-sporting-possess-as-aberdeen-suffer-another-europa-league-near-miss/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027151743/https://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/fp/sport/football/aberdeen-fc/2518114/fan-view-tiago-tomas-finish-showed-strength-sporting-possess-as-aberdeen-suffer-another-europa-league-near-miss/ |archive-date=27 October 2020 |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=Press and Journal |language=en-GB}}</ref> After arriving in [[Lisbon]] at the ''[[Estádio José Alvalade]]'' under some suspicion for young age, Porro immediately established himself as starter in the right side of the defence, making his league debut in a 2–0 away victory against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20202021/liganos/2/2|title=Liga NOS – Jornada 2 – FC P.Ferreira vs Sporting CP|website=[[Primeira Liga]]|access-date=21 November 2021|language=pt|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121144441/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20202021/liganos/2/2|archive-date=21 November 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the ''Leões'' on 1 November in a 4–0 victory against [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvi24.iol.pt/sporting/pote/goleadores-pedro-goncalves-ja-e-o-segundo-melhor-marcador-da-liga|title=Pedro Gonçalves já é o segundo melhor marcador da Liga|trans-title=Pedro Gonçalves is already the League's second highest scorer|website=[[CNN Portugal]]|publisher=[[Media Capital]]|language=pt|date=1 November 2020|access-date=4 November 2020|archive-date=21 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121145956/https://tvi24.iol.pt/sporting/pote/goleadores-pedro-goncalves-ja-e-o-segundo-melhor-marcador-da-liga|url-status=live}}</ref> For his outstanding performances for the club, Porro was named the [[Primeira Liga]]'s Defender of the Month for three consecutive months, between [[2020–21 Primeira Liga#Awards|November]] and [[2020–21 Primeira Liga#Awards|January 2021]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Best of December 2020–21: Sérgio Oliveira and Crespo are the highlights of the month|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20202021/noticias/geral/premios/dezembro/melhores-de-dezembro-2020-21-sergio-oliveira-e-crespo-em-destaque/|access-date=13 March 2021|website=Primeira Liga|archive-date=9 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210509201131/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20202021/noticias/geral/premios/dezembro/melhores-de-dezembro-2020-21-sergio-oliveira-e-crespo-em-destaque/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 January, Porro scored the only goal in the defeat of [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] to help his club [[2020–21 Taça da Liga|win]] the [[Taça da Liga]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20210123/6193895/espanol-pedro-porro-da-sporting-portugal-copa-liga.html | title = Spanish Pedro Porro gives Sporting de Portugal the League Cup|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|publisher = [[Grupo Godó]]| date =23 January 2021 | access-date =23 January 2021 | archive-date=23 January 2021 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210123221519/https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20210123/6193895/espanol-pedro-porro-da-sporting-portugal-copa-liga.html | url-status = live }}</ref> Three days later, Porro scored a shot outside the box, in a 2–0 away victory against [[FC Boavista|Boavista]]. His strike was later voted as the Primeira Liga's Goal of the Month.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/video-bomba-de-pedro-porro-e-o-melhor-golo-do-mes-de-janeiro-na-i-liga | title = VÍdeo: 'Bomba' de Pedro Porro é o Melhor Golo do Mês de janeiro na I Liga|website= Sapo Desporto|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|date=12 February 2021 | access-date=12 February 2021|language=pt|archive-date=12 February 2021 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210212190008/https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/video-bomba-de-pedro-porro-e-o-melhor-golo-do-mes-de-janeiro-na-i-liga | url-status = live }}</ref> He played 30 games for the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga|eventual champions]], ending a 19-year drought, while also being named in the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Team of the Year]].<ref name="PL">{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2080-10-reasons-why-sporting-are-champions-of-portugal|title=10 reasons why Sporting are Champions of Portugal|website=PortuGOAL|first=Tom|last=Kundert|date=11 May 2021|access-date=25 May 2021|archive-date=12 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512123545/https://portugoal.net/club-news/2080-10-reasons-why-sporting-are-champions-of-portugal|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/joao-palhinha-do-sporting-no-melhor-onze-da-ultima-edicao-da-i-liga-13814732.html|title=João Palhinha, do Sporting, no melhor onze da última edição da I Liga|trans-title=João Palhinha, of Sporting, in the All-Star XI of I League's last edition|publisher=[[TSF (radio station)|TSF]]|language=pt|date=8 June 2021|access-date=21 October 2021|archive-date=21 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021091820/https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/joao-palhinha-do-sporting-no-melhor-onze-da-ultima-edicao-da-i-liga-13814732.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the beginning of the [[2021–22 Sporting CP season|following season]], Porro continued with outstanding performances, providing an assist for [[Nuno Santos (footballer, born 1995)|Nuno Santos]] in a 1–1 home draw against Sporting's [[FC Porto–Sporting CP rivalry|rivals]] [[FC Porto|Porto]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20212022/ligaportugalbwin/5/1|title=Liga Portugal bwin – Jornada 5 – Sporting CP vs FC Porto|website=Primeira Liga|access-date=21 November 2021|language=pt|archive-date=21 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121151903/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20212022/ligaportugalbwin/5/1|url-status=live}}</ref> and scored two goals from the penalty spot on two consecutive league games – in a 1–0 victory against [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] on 19 September and a 1–0 victory against [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]] on 24 September – which earned him the Primeira Liga's Defender of the Month award for two consecutive months in August and September.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Best of September/October 2020–21: Pedro Gonçalves and Gonçalo Ramos are the highlights of the month|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20202021/noticias/geral/premios/setembrooutubro/melhores-de-setembrooutubro-2020-21-pedro-goncalves-e-goncalo-ramos-em-destaque/|access-date=13 March 2021|website=Primeira Liga|archive-date=26 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026171826/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20202021/noticias/geral/premios/setembrooutubro/melhores-de-setembrooutubro-2020-21-pedro-goncalves-e-goncalo-ramos-em-destaque/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 24 November, Porro scored the third goal against [[Borussia Dortmund]] in a 3–1 home victory at a group stage match of the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League]], by converting the rebound after [[Gregor Kobel]] saved a penalty from [[Pedro Gonçalves]], to ensure his team qualification to the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of sixteen]], for the first time since the [[2008–09 UEFA Champions League|2008–09]] season.<ref>{{cite news|last=Vasa|first=Marco|date=24 November 2021|title=Sporting aprendeu a ser feliz na Champions|trans-title=Sporting learned to be happy in the Champions|url=https://www.publico.pt/2021/11/24/desporto/noticia/sporting-vence-borussia-qualificase-champions-1986288|language=pt|newspaper=[[Público (Portugal)|Público]]|access-date=24 November 2021|archive-date=24 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124224851/https://www.publico.pt/2021/11/24/desporto/noticia/sporting-vence-borussia-qualificase-champions-1986288|url-status=live}}</ref> Shortly afterwards, Porro began suffering from recurring hamstring injuries, which sidelined him for two months of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 December 2021 |title=Pedro Porro lesiona-se e 'vira' dor de cabeça para Rúben Amorim |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1892153/pedro-porro-lesiona-se-e-vira-dor-de-cabea-para-rben-amorim |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220202203933/https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1892153/pedro-porro-lesiona-se-e-vira-dor-de-cabea-para-rben-amorim |archive-date=2 February 2022 |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=Notícias ao Minuto |language=pt}}</ref> He made his return from injury on 29 January 2022, with his crucial assist to [[Pablo Sarabia]] helping his team come from behind to defeat [[Lisbon derby|crosstown rivals]] [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] 2–1 in the [[2022 Taça da Liga final|2021–22 Taça da Liga final]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ribeiro |first=Patrick |date=29 January 2022 |title=Sporting defend their Taça da Liga title in second-half turnaround versus Benfica |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2426-sporting-defend-their-taca-da-liga-title-in-second-half-turnaround-versus-benfica |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220130163751/https://portugoal.net/club-news/2426-sporting-defend-their-taca-da-liga-title-in-second-half-turnaround-versus-benfica |archive-date=30 January 2022 |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=portugoal.net}}</ref>

On 16 May 2022, Sporting triggered Porro's buyout clause of €8.5m (£7.2m) million, signing him on a permanent three-year deal with a reported €20m (£17.6m) million buy-back clause.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sporting/16-05-2022/oficial-sporting-aciona-opcao-de-compra-por-porro | title=Official: Sporting aciona opção de compra por Porro|website=Mais Futebol|date=16 May 2022|access-date=17 May 2022|language=pt| archive-date=17 May 2022| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517102324/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sporting/16-05-2022/oficial-sporting-aciona-opcao-de-compra-por-porro | url-status=live }}</ref> Following a season in which he helped Sporting to a runner-up finish behind rivals Porto, scoring five goals and providing seven assists, he was named in the [[2021–22 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Team of the Year]] for a second consecutive season.<ref name=TOTS>{{Cite web|title=Liga Nos Team of the season|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-06-28/liga-taremi-fecha-onze-do-ano-da-liga-os-eleitos-por-treinadores-e-capitaes-fot/947237|access-date=29 June 2022|website=[[A Bola]]|language=pt|archive-date=29 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220629223413/https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-06-28/liga-taremi-fecha-onze-do-ano-da-liga-os-eleitos-por-treinadores-e-capitaes-fot/947237|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Tottenham Hotspur ===
On 31 January 2023, the deadline day of the transfer window, [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] announced the signing of Porro on loan from Sporting for a loan fee of €5&nbsp;million,<ref>{{Cite news |date=31 January 2023 |title=Tottenham sign Pedro Porro from Sporting Lisbon |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4141507/2023/01/31/tottenham-pedro-porro-deadline-day/ |access-date=2025-04-11 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> with an obligation to buy in the summer for €40&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/january/porro-signs-from-sporting/|title=Porro signs from Sporting|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=31 January 2023|access-date=31 January 2023|archive-date=31 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131225741/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/january/porro-signs-from-sporting/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |date=31 January 2023 |title=Tottenham complete Pedro Porro signing from Sporting in €45m deal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jan/31/tottenham-set-to-complete-signing-of-pedro-porro-from-sporting |access-date=2025-04-11 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> In return, Sporting also received 15% of [[Marcus Edwards]]' economic rights.<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 November 2023 |title=Sporting divulga números do mercado de transferências |trans-title=Sporting discloses transfer market numbers |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/sporting-divulga-numeros-do-mercado-de-transferencias-2023111515540109816 |access-date=15 November 2023|website=A Bola|publisher=[[Ringier]]|language=pt}}</ref>

Porro made his Spurs debut on 11 February, starting in a 4–1 defeat to [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Emlyn|last=Begley|title=Leicester come back to blow away sloppy Spurs|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64520925|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC |access-date=11 February 2023|archive-date=11 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230211174125/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64520925 |url-status=live }}</ref> His performance drew criticism from former Spurs manager [[Tim Sherwood]], who described Porro as "so bad it's unbelievable."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Verri |first=Matt |date=13 February 2023|title=Spurs defender slammed as Levy questioned: 'So bad it's unbelievable' |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/pedro-porro-tim-sherwood-daniel-levy-tottenham-signing-b1059835.html |access-date=20 February 2023|website=Evening Standard|archive-date=20 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230220122847/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/pedro-porro-tim-sherwood-daniel-levy-tottenham-signing-b1059835.html |url-status=live }}</ref> However, he scored his first goal for the club on 18 March 2023 in a 3–3 away draw at [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] and went from strength to strength.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Jess|last=Anderson|title=Southampton v Tottenham Hotspur|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64923719|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=18 March 2023|archive-date=17 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230317213556/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64923719 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 5 January 2024, Porro scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in the [[2023–24 FA Cup|FA Cup]] third round.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Michael|last=Emmons|title=Tottenham Hotspur v Burnley|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67886952|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=5 January 2024|access-date=5 April 2025}}</ref>

On 8 May 2025, Porro scored the final goal in a 2–0 second-leg victory against [[FK Bodø/Glimt]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League]] semi-final to secure a 5–1 aggregate victory, sending Spurs into the [[2025 UEFA Europa League final|final]], which Spurs won 1–0.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0299-1db5e5ef39fc-01b76bc21f6a-1000--bodo-glimt-0-2-tottenham-agg-1-5-spurs-ease-into-europa-le/|title=
Bodø/Glimt 0–2 Tottenham (agg: 1–5): Spurs ease into Europa League final|publisher=UEFA|date=8 May 2025|accessdate=8 May 2025}}</ref> For his performances throughout the tournament, Porro was named in the Europa League Team of the Season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=The official website for European football |url=https://www.uefa.com/errors/ |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2019, Porro received his first call-up for [[Spain national football team|Spain]] at [[Spain national under-21 football team|under-21 level]], making his debut on 29 March in a 1–0 friendly victory against [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.marca.com/futbol/seleccion/2019/03/21/5c93bdfe268e3e6b758b45ba.html|first=Javier|last=Estepa|title=España Sub21 vs Rumanía Sub21, en directo|trans-title=Spain U21 vs Romania U21, direct|access-date = 21 March 2019 | date = 21 March 2019 | website = Marca|location=Spain|language = es| archive-date = 21 March 2019 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190321193903/https://www.marca.com/futbol/seleccion/2019/03/21/5c93bdfe268e3e6b758b45ba.html | url-status = live }}</ref> In March 2021, he received his first call-up to the [[Spain national football team]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group B|group stage]] of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Official: I Esta es la convocatoria de la Selección Española para los primeros partidos de la fase de clasificación para el Mundial de Catar 2022|url=https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-i-esta-es-convocatoria-seleccion-espanola-primeros-partidos-fase-clasificacion-mundial-catar|publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation|access-date=25 March 2021|language=es|archive-date=30 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210330174024/https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-i-esta-es-convocatoria-seleccion-espanola-primeros-partidos-fase-clasificacion-mundial-catar|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut on 28 March 2021 in a 2–1 victory against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Domeque |first=Estrella |date=30 March 2021 |title=Pedro Porro: "Es un orgullo enorme llevar a Extremadura a lo más alto" |trans-title=Pedro Porro: "It’s a tremendous honor to take Extremadura to the top" |url=https://www.hoy.es/deportes/futbol/seleccion-espanola/pedro-porro-orgullo-20210330221008-nt.html?vca=dgtk-rrss-hoy&vmc=social&vso=fb |access-date=2025-04-11 |website=Hoy |language=es}}</ref>

